                <body>
                    

 Oglaigh Tiormhala na  h-Eireann:- Irish National Volunteers.<lb/> <opener><address><addrLine>Inspector General's Office,</addrLine>
<addrLine>44 PARNELL SQUARE,</addrLine>
<addrLine>DUBLIN.</addrLine></address></opener>   telephone 4598 Dublin <lb/>  telegrams Volunteers <lb/>  201. <lb/>  ALL COMMUNICATIONS TO BE <lb/>  ADDRESSED TO <lb/>   THE INSPECTOR GENERAL. <lb/> <date>Date, 4th. May, 1916. </date>  <address>His  Excellency,<lb/> The Lord Lieutenant, <lb/>  Dublin Castle.</address>  <salute>May it please your Excellency,</salute>  <p>Several cases have been reported to me of Officers and <lb/>  other members of the National Volunteers who have been arrested by the <lb/>  Military authorities and who are still detained.</p>   <p>In drawing your Excellency's  attention to this matter I fully <lb/>  recognise the serious difficulties the Military Authorities have , and the <lb/>  impossibility of avoiding the arrest of perfectly innocent persons, In the <lb/>  course of my inquiries regarding several persons who are under arrest <lb/>  I discovered that amongst some senior officers of the Military the opinion <lb/>  prevailed that the Sinn Feiners and the National Volunteers were branches <lb/>  of the same body. As there is not the remotest ground for such belief I <lb/>  hope your Excellency will agree that it would be advisable that the Military <lb/>  Authorities<lb/> should know that such is not the case and that there is no <lb/>  connection whatever between the National Volunteers (under the leadership  of Mr John Redmond M.P. ) and the Sinn Fein Volunteers.</p> <p>I would ask Your Excellency to make representation to such author- <lb/>  ity as you may think proper regarding the matter referred to.</p> <p>I might further add that in the case of arrests of suspects and where <pb/>
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="4684" facs="#L1916_1864_img_4684"/>
        
        
           
            the person states that he is a member of the National Volunteers <lb/>  I shall be glad to place at the disposal of authorities <lb/>  responsible officers who will be in a position to verify or <lb/>  otherwise the statements made by suspected persons and furnish <lb/>  information which the Military authorities may require regarding same.</p>  <closer><salute>I have the honour to be,<lb/>  Your Excellency's obedient servant</salute></closer>   J. Crean Major <lb/>  Acting Inspector General.
        
    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        
            
        

         

